One cannot control what others do with one's body a=
fter one leaves it. So 
the wisest course of action would be to develop det=
achment even when alive.
 
Divert the concern for the well-being of the bod=
y towards other people. Do 
bare minimum to keep the body alive and not be =
overly concerned about it. 
When you meditate, think only of god and try to=
 forget that there is a body 
that you occupy. Even if leg hurts or neck it=
ches, try to forget about it. 
If you ignore body for a while, it will cry =
out for attention, like an 
immature child who needs attention. If you give=
 it attention, you cannot 
experience god. But, as you ignore body more, bo=
dy will try more to get your 
attention (like an immature child who needs a=
ttention)! However, if you 
persist, body will have to eventually give up! =
THAT is when one can absorb 
the mind fully in god.

If one experiences tha=
t often while alive, that experience helps immensely 
at death. When the mi=
nd leaves the body for the last time, one can focus 
mind on god and ignore=
 the attention grabbing cries for help from the
 body. 
