ogi, each session of deep meditation is like a dress rehearsal of the 
last=
 moment! Death is not to be feared. If faced correctly, it is the moment 
o=
f final liberation. Life is meant to be a practice for it!

Instead of worr=
ying about body and its last rites, let every ritual be a 
last rite! I sug=
gest that one should practice detachment and develop the 
ability to absolu=
tely ignore the pitiful cries of the body for attention as 
one tries to fo=
cus the mind on god and succeed in absorbing the mind in god 
when meditati=
ng. If one practices that, the issue of who does last rites and 
what rites=
 becomes irrelevant.

